sense.def: an African animal like a horse with black and white lines
dictionaryExamples: We saw a zebra in the distance.
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: Otherwise there would be many children and grown-ups who had never seen an elephant, a tiger, a zebra etc. First Certificate in English; B2; Danish

dictionaryExamples: Five, four, three, two, one, zero.

sense.def: the temperature that is 32 degrees lower than the temperature at which water freezes in degrees Fahrenheit, or the temperature at which water freezes in degrees centigrade
dictionaryExamples: In the winter, the temperature can drop to 15 degrees below zero.
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: We have to learn that [it] is not natural for a lion [to live] in a country where, in winter, [the] temperature can fall below zero. (583941; First Certificate in English; Italy; B2 VANTAGE; 1993; Italian; Fail

sense.def: a thing for fastening clothes, bags, etc. consisting of two rows of very small parts that connect together
dictionaryExamples: The jeans had two buttons and a zipper in front.
I can't open my bag - the zipper is stuck.
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: In conclusion, I believe that common clothes in the future will be overalls without buttons or zippers, that you easily slip into, which also are very comfortable. First Certificate in English; B2; Swedish

sense.def: an area where a particular thing happens, that is used for a particular purpose, or where there are particular rules
dictionaryExamples: He was charged with driving 75 mph in a 55 mph zone.
The UN Security Council has established a no-fly zone.
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: It is a very clean city with a lot of car-free zones. Preliminary English Test; B1; Swiss German

sense.def: a place where  wild animals are kept so that people can go and look at them
dictionaryExamples: I love going  to the zoo.
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: So I went to see the animals in the zoo, my daughter the ducks, and I enjoyed when I s[aw] my daughter very happy playing with the ducks. Skills for Life (Entry 1); A1; [no L1 data]

sense.def: a long green vegetable that is white inside
dictionaryExamples: We had grilled zucchini, peppers, and mushrooms  with rice for dinner.
newly ripe tomatoes, zucchinis, and watermelons
sense.learnerExample: Learner example: My fav[o]rite, it's one with the mushrooms and zucchini. Preliminary English Test; B1; Italian
